message.content:
cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a relay network and the age of updates in such a network. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses queuing theory tools to provide a closed form of the average age for both streams. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the case where the server has other tasks to fulfill and examines the age process of the stream of interest. 
4. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper aims to optimize the generation rate of packets belonging to each stream to achieve the minimum possible average age. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper provides insights on more general multi-hop scenarios.
